"use strict";(self.webpackChunk_N_E=self.webpackChunk_N_E||[]).push([[381],{2381:function(e,t,o){o.r(t),o.d(t,{CANNONWRIGHT:function(){return n}});let n={id:"cannonwright",title:"The Cannonwright Pirate",shortDescription:"Obsessed with explosions and black powder inventions.",skillGrid:{exploration:["star","open","open","star","blocked","blocked","blocked"],brawn:["star","open","open","star","star","blocked","blocked"],hunting:["star","star","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked"],aim:["star","open","open","star","star","star","blocked"],swagger:["open","open","star","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked"],navigation:["star","star","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked"]},constellation:o(9774).Pd,storyBlanks:[{number:1,prompt:"A nickname for your favorite cannon",type:"text"},{number:2,prompt:"A fancy word for an explosion",type:"text"},{number:3,prompt:"Your dream invention",type:"text"},{number:4,prompt:"The pirate name of another player",type:"player_name"},{number:5,prompt:"A funny word for failure",type:"text"}],backstory:"BOOM! That's my favorite sound. The sound of a cannon firin', of black powder ignitin', of a ship's hull splinterin' into a thousand pieces. I've been obsessed with cannons since I was a wee lad, when my da' took me to see the royal cannon factory. I was mesmerized by the power, the noise, the beautiful destructive force of it all. I named my first cannon {1} and I've been buildin' and firin' 'em ever since.\n\nThe other pirates think I'm a bit mad, and maybe they're right. But when the battle starts and {1} starts singin', they're all happy enough to have me around. I've been workin' on a new invention I call the {3}, which I reckon will revolutionize naval warfare. If I can just get the black powder ratios right, it'll be the most spectacular {2} anyone's ever seen. Or the most spectacular {5}. Either way, it'll be loud.\n\nI signed up with this crew because they promised me access to rare materials and exotic islands where I might find new components for my experiments. Plus, {4} told me there'd be plenty of things to blow up. That was all I needed to hear.",events:[{narrative:"I found some rare minerals on the last island we visited. Mixed with black powder, they create a blast twice as powerful as normal! I call it Super {2} Powder. The test run scared half the crew, but {4} said it was the most beautiful thing they'd ever seen. I couldn't agree more.",effect:"Retrieve card 31 Superior Cannon from the story deck."},{narrative:"My latest experiment was a {5}. Well, sort of. The {3} prototype exploded, but in the process it blew a hole in the enemy ship that was about to attack us. Sometimes failure IS the best teacher!",effect:"Infamy +2. Discard 1 misfortune token."},{narrative:"I've been tinkerin' with {1} and I think I've finally figured out how to increase the range. A few modifications here and there, and now my beloved cannon can hit targets that are practically over the horizon. The cap'n was impressed, and the crew gave me a round of applause. Best day ever.",effect:"Gain 1 skill of your choice. Re-roll +1."},{narrative:"{4} helped me test the new fuses today. They were surprisingly useful for someone who usually just stands around lookin' confused. Together we managed to fire off {1} twelve times in a row without a misfire. A new record!",effect:"Crew +1. Infamy +1."},{narrative:"I found plans for an ancient weapon in a chest on a deserted island. It's similar to my {3} but far more advanced. The ancients were clearly ahead of their time. I'm goin' to use these plans to improve my own designs.",effect:"Treasure +1. Re-roll +2."}],endings:{bad:{threshold:"≤3",text:"Your obsession with {1} and your experiments with the {3} finally catch up with you. One night, while trying to create the perfect {2}, you accidentally set fire to the ship's powder stores. The resulting explosion is indeed the most spectacular anyone has ever seen, but unfortunately you're at the center of it. They find your favorite wrench three islands away. {4} writes a lovely eulogy that mentions your passion for loud noises and your complete disregard for safety protocols. Your grave marker reads: \"Here lies the Cannonwright. They went out with a bang. Literally.\""},good:{threshold:"4",text:"After your pirating days, you open a cannon foundry called The {2} Works, where you build the finest cannons in all the land. Pirates from everywhere come to buy your wares, and {1} becomes the most famous cannon in history after you mount it at the entrance as a display piece. Your {3} never quite works as intended, but a scaled-down version becomes a popular children's toy, which is mildly concerning. {4} becomes your business partner, handling the books while you handle the booms. It's not the most glamorous life, but every morning you wake up to the smell of black powder, and that's all you ever wanted."},legendary:{threshold:"5",text:"You finally perfect the {3}, and it changes the world. Nations and pirate fleets alike clamor for your invention, and you become the most sought-after weaponsmith in all of Sunset. You use your wealth and fame to establish the Royal Institute of {2}, a prestigious academy dedicated to the science of controlled explosions. Your masterwork, a golden version of {1}, sits in the institute's main hall, and students come from across the world to study under you. {4} becomes the dean of students, a role they take to with surprising competence. In your twilight years, you sit on the institute's balcony, watching your students test their experiments on the practice range below. Every boom makes you smile. You have turned your passion into a legacy, and the world is louder for it."}}}}}]);